Vice President Kamala Harris visited Applied Materials Headquarters in Sunnyvale, California to announce that the company will invest up to an additional $4 billion to build a new semiconductor research and development facility. This facility, once completed, will be the largest of its kind in the world. The Vice President highlighted the importance of semiconductors in modern technology and emphasized the need for more compact, efficient, powerful, and affordable semiconductors to support future advancements in areas such as renewable energy, high-speed internet, artificial intelligence, and healthcare. She also mentioned the investments made by the administration in semiconductor research and development, as well as semiconductor manufacturing, to strengthen national security and create jobs. Overall, the Vice President emphasized the importance of investing in America's innovation and expressed confidence in the country's ability to achieve greatness.